The author, a former United States Senator, reflects on the importance of religious freedom and the need to protect it. They highlight the rise of discrimination and violence against religious minorities in the United States and around the world. The author discusses various actions taken by their administration to defend religious freedom, including rescinding the travel ban against majority-Muslim countries, countering Islamophobia and antisemitism, increasing funding for the security of nonprofits, and providing financial assistance to victims of religious repression. They emphasize the commitment to promoting religious freedom and ensuring that people of all religions, or no religion, can practice their faith without fear.